The Ongea SummitÂ ran from Friday to Sunday at New Sarit Expo Centre. It was free of charge. The event is held to support talent and open doors to upcoming artistes. Present were Culture CS Amina Mohamed and PS Jospeta Mukobe, who were very impressed with what the youths are doing in the music industry. Renowned artistes like Joyce Omondi, Tetu Shani and Ben Soul entertained the audience. The main sponsors for the event were Radio Africa Group and Switch TV.